# Java vs Node.js vs Python — Complete Side-by-Side Reference

> 💡 **How to practice:** Type each snippet by hand. One concept per day across all 3 languages.

---

## 1. Variables & Types

| Concept | Java | Node.js | Python |
|---|---|---|---|
| Declare | `int x = 10;` | `let x = 10;` | `x = 10` |
| Constant | `final int X = 10;` | `const X = 10;` | `X = 10` (convention) |
| Null | `null` | `null` / `undefined` | `None` |
| Type Check | `x instanceof Integer` | `typeof x === "number"` | `isinstance(x, int)` |
| Type Cast | `(int) 3.9` | `parseInt("42")` | `int("42")` |

### 🧪 Practice
```java
// Java
int age = 25;
double pi = 3.14;
boolean flag = true;
System.out.println(age instanceof Integer); // true
```
```javascript
// Node.js
let age = 25;
const pi = 3.14;
let flag = true;
console.log(typeof age === "number"); // true
```
```python
# Python
age = 25
pi = 3.14
flag = True
print(isinstance(age, int))  # True
```

