## 3. Control Flow

| Concept | Java | Node.js | Python |
|---|---|---|---|
| If/Else | `if (x > 0) {}` | `if (x > 0) {}` | `if x > 0:` |
| Ternary | `x > 0 ? "pos" : "neg"` | `x > 0 ? "pos" : "neg"` | `"pos" if x > 0 else "neg"` |
| Switch | `switch(x) { case 1: }` | `switch(x) { case 1: }` | `match x: case 1:` (3.10+) |

### 🧪 Practice
```java
// Java
int score = 85;
if (score >= 90) {
    System.out.println("A");
} else if (score >= 80) {
    System.out.println("B");
} else {
    System.out.println("C");
}

String day = "Mon";
switch (day) {
    case "Mon": System.out.println("Start"); break;
    case "Fri": System.out.println("End");   break;
    default:    System.out.println("Mid");
}
```
```javascript
// Node.js
let score = 85;
if (score >= 90) console.log("A");
else if (score >= 80) console.log("B");
else console.log("C");

let day = "Mon";
switch (day) {
    case "Mon": console.log("Start"); break;
    case "Fri": console.log("End");   break;
    default:    console.log("Mid");
}
```
```python
# Python
score = 85
if score >= 90:
    print("A")
elif score >= 80:
    print("B")
else:
    print("C")

day = "Mon"
match day:
    case "Mon": print("Start")
    case "Fri": print("End")
    case _:     print("Mid")
```

