## 6. OOP

| Concept | Java | Node.js | Python |
|---|---|---|---|
| Class | `public class Dog {}` | `class Dog {}` | `class Dog:` |
| Constructor | `public Dog(String name)` | `constructor(name)` | `def __init__(self, name):` |
| Inheritance | `class Lab extends Dog` | `class Lab extends Dog` | `class Lab(Dog):` |
| Override | `@Override` | (implicit) | (implicit) |
| Static | `static void hello()` | `static hello()` | `@staticmethod` |
| this/self | `this` | `this` | `self` (explicit) |
| Super | `super.method()` | `super.method()` | `super().method()` |
| Access | `public/private/protected` | `_convention` | `_convention` |

### 🧪 Practice
```java
// Java
class Animal {
    String name;
    Animal(String name) { this.name = name; }
    String speak() { return "..."; }
}
class Cat extends Animal {
    Cat(String name) { super(name); }
    @Override
    String speak() { return name + " says Meow"; }
}
Cat c = new Cat("Luna");
System.out.println(c.speak()); // Luna says Meow
```
```javascript
// Node.js
class Animal {
    constructor(name) { this.name = name; }
    speak() { return "..."; }
}
class Cat extends Animal {
    speak() { return `${this.name} says Meow`; }
}
const c = new Cat("Luna");
console.log(c.speak()); // Luna says Meow
```
```python
# Python
class Animal:
    def __init__(self, name):
        self.name = name
    def speak(self):
        return "..."

class Cat(Animal):
    def speak(self):
        return f"{self.name} says Meow"

c = Cat("Luna")
print(c.speak())  # Luna says Meow
```

