## 7. Collections

| Concept | Java | Node.js | Python |
|---|---|---|---|
| Create List | `new ArrayList<>()` | `[]` | `[]` |
| Add | `list.add(x)` | `arr.push(x)` | `list.append(x)` |
| Remove | `list.remove(x)` | `arr.splice(i,1)` | `list.remove(x)` |
| Contains | `list.contains(x)` | `arr.includes(x)` | `x in list` |
| Length | `list.size()` | `arr.length` | `len(list)` |
| Sort | `Collections.sort(list)` | `arr.sort()` | `list.sort()` |
| Slice | `list.subList(0,3)` | `arr.slice(0,3)` | `lst[0:3]` |
| Map | `stream().map(fn)` | `arr.map(fn)` | `[f(x) for x in lst]` |
| Filter | `stream().filter(fn)` | `arr.filter(fn)` | `[x for x in lst if f(x)]` |
| Reduce | `stream().reduce(0, fn)` | `arr.reduce(fn, init)` | `functools.reduce(fn, lst)` |

### 🧪 Practice
```java
// Java
List<Integer> nums = new ArrayList<>(Arrays.asList(3, 1, 4, 1, 5));
nums.add(9);
Collections.sort(nums); // [1, 1, 3, 4, 5, 9]

// Map → square each
List<Integer> squared = nums.stream()
    .map(x -> x * x)
    .collect(Collectors.toList());

// Filter → evens only
List<Integer> evens = nums.stream()
    .filter(x -> x % 2 == 0)
    .collect(Collectors.toList());

// Reduce → sum
int total = nums.stream().reduce(0, Integer::sum);

// Map (HashMap)
Map<String, Integer> scores = new HashMap<>();
scores.put("Alice", 95);
scores.put("Bob", 87);
System.out.println(scores.get("Alice")); // 95
```
```javascript
// Node.js
let nums = [3, 1, 4, 1, 5];
nums.push(9);
nums.sort((a, b) => a - b); // [1, 1, 3, 4, 5, 9]

const squared = nums.map(x => x * x);
const evens   = nums.filter(x => x % 2 === 0);
const total   = nums.reduce((acc, x) => acc + x, 0);

const scores = { Alice: 95, Bob: 87 };
console.log(scores["Alice"]); // 95
```
```python
# Python
nums = [3, 1, 4, 1, 5]
nums.append(9)
nums.sort()  # [1, 1, 3, 4, 5, 9]

squared = [x * x for x in nums]
evens   = [x for x in nums if x % 2 == 0]

from functools import reduce
total = reduce(lambda a, x: a + x, nums)

scores = {"Alice": 95, "Bob": 87}
print(scores["Alice"])  # 95
```

