## 8. Error Handling

| Concept | Java | Node.js | Python |
|---|---|---|---|
| Try/Catch | `try {} catch(Exception e) {}` | `try {} catch(e) {}` | `try: except Exception as e:` |
| Finally | `finally {}` | `finally {}` | `finally:` |
| Throw | `throw new Exception("msg")` | `throw new Error("msg")` | `raise ValueError("msg")` |
| Custom Error | `class E extends Exception` | `class E extends Error` | `class E(Exception):` |
| Checked | Yes (must declare/catch) | No | No |

### 🧪 Practice
```java
// Java
try {
    int x = 10 / 0;
} catch (ArithmeticException e) {
    System.out.println("Error: " + e.getMessage());
} finally {
    System.out.println("done");
}

// Custom exception
class AppError extends RuntimeException {
    public AppError(String msg) { super(msg); }
}
throw new AppError("Bad input");
```
```javascript
// Node.js
try {
    let x = JSON.parse("{bad}");
} catch (e) {
    console.log("Error: " + e.message);
} finally {
    console.log("done");
}

// Custom exception
class AppError extends Error {
    constructor(msg) { super(msg); this.name = "AppError"; }
}
throw new AppError("Bad input");
```
```python
# Python
try:
    x = int("abc")
except ValueError as e:
    print(f"Error: {e}")
finally:
    print("done")

# Custom exception
class AppError(Exception): pass
raise AppError("Bad input")
```

