## 9. Async / Concurrency

| Concept | Java | Node.js | Python |
|---|---|---|---|
| Async Model | `CompletableFuture` | Event loop (single-threaded) | `asyncio` |
| Async/Await | Via `CompletableFuture` | `async/await` (native) | `async/await` (native) |
| Parallel | `ExecutorService` | `Promise.all([...])` | `asyncio.gather(*tasks)` |
| Threads | `Thread` / `ExecutorService` | `Worker Threads` | `threading.Thread` |
| GIL | No GIL | No GIL | Has GIL (CPython) |

### 🧪 Practice
```java
// Java
CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> "data")
    .thenAccept(d -> System.out.println("Got: " + d));

// Parallel
ExecutorService pool = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(2);
pool.submit(() -> System.out.println("Task 1"));
pool.submit(() -> System.out.println("Task 2"));
pool.shutdown();
```
```javascript
// Node.js
async function fetchData() {
    const res  = await fetch("https://api.example.com/data");
    const data = await res.json();
    return data;
}

// Parallel
const [a, b] = await Promise.all([fetchA(), fetchB()]);
```
```python
# Python
import asyncio

async def fetch():
    await asyncio.sleep(1)
    return "data"

# Parallel
async def main():
    a, b = await asyncio.gather(taskA(), taskB())

asyncio.run(main())
```

