## 10. File I/O & JSON

| Concept | Java | Node.js | Python |
|---|---|---|---|
| Write File | `Files.writeString(path, str)` | `fs.writeFileSync("f.txt", s)` | `open("f.txt","w").write(s)` |
| Read File | `Files.readString(path)` | `fs.readFileSync("f.txt","utf8")` | `open("f.txt").read()` |
| JSON Parse | `objectMapper.readValue(json, T)` | `JSON.parse(str)` | `json.loads(str)` |
| JSON Stringify | `objectMapper.writeValueAsString(obj)` | `JSON.stringify(obj)` | `json.dumps(obj)` |

### 🧪 Practice
```java
// Java
import java.nio.file.*;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;

// Write / Read
Files.writeString(Path.of("f.txt"), "hello");
String txt = Files.readString(Path.of("f.txt"));

// JSON
ObjectMapper m = new ObjectMapper();
String json = m.writeValueAsString(Map.of("name", "Mani", "age", 30));
Map obj = m.readValue(json, Map.class);
```
```javascript
// Node.js
const fs = require("fs");

fs.writeFileSync("f.txt", "hello");
const txt = fs.readFileSync("f.txt", "utf8");

const json = JSON.stringify({ name: "Mani", age: 30 });
const obj  = JSON.parse(json);
console.log(obj.name); // Mani
```
```python
# Python
import json

with open("f.txt", "w") as f: f.write("hello")
with open("f.txt") as f: txt = f.read()

json_str = json.dumps({"name": "Mani", "age": 30})
obj = json.loads(json_str)
print(obj["name"])  # Mani
```

